# Frontend stack

Next.js 15 · React 19 · TypeScript 5 · Tailwind CSS v4 · Radix UI · App Router
State: Zustand (UI only) · Forms: React Hook Form + Zod
Auth: next-auth session cookies (NOT JWT/Bearer) · Payments: Stripe.js Elements
Icons: React Icons / Lucide React · Images: Cloudinary (signed uploads)

# The most important rule — where things live

```
app/           → ONLY routing files: page.tsx, layout.tsx, loading.tsx, error.tsx, not-found.tsx
features/      → ALL components organized by domain
components/    → ONLY truly shared UI (used in 3+ features)
lib/api/       → ALL fetch calls to Django API
store/         → Zustand UI state only
```

**There are NO `_components` folders inside `app/`.** That was the main problem in the old project. If a component exists, it goes in `features/{domain}/components/`, not next to its page.

