# Server Components vs Client Components — the core rule

**Every component is a Server Component by default.**
Add `'use client'` ONLY when the component needs: browser events, useState, useEffect, browser APIs.

```typescript
// app/catalogo/page.tsx — Server Component (no 'use client')
// Can fetch data directly, has access to cookies/headers
import { getProducts } from "@/lib/api/products"
import { ProductGrid } from "@/features/catalog/components/ProductGrid"

export default async function CatalogPage({ searchParams }) {
  const products = await getProducts(searchParams)  // server-side fetch
  return <ProductGrid products={products} />
}

// features/catalog/components/FilterSheet.tsx — Client Component
"use client"  // needs state for open/close, user interaction
import { useState } from "react"

export function FilterSheet() {
  const [isOpen, setIsOpen] = useState(false)
  ...
}
```

**Rule:** if you need `useState`, `useEffect`, `onClick`, `onChange` → `'use client'`.
If you only render data → Server Component, no directive needed.

# Special files — use them, don't skip them

```typescript
// app/(site)/(public)/catalogo/loading.tsx — shown while page.tsx fetches
export default function CatalogLoading() {
  return <ProductGridSkeleton />
}

// app/(site)/(public)/catalogo/error.tsx — shown on fetch error
"use client"
export default function CatalogError({ error, reset }) {
  return <ErrorState message="No pudimos cargar los productos." onRetry={reset} />
}

// app/not-found.tsx — shown on 404
export default function NotFound() {
  return <div>Página no encontrada</div>
}
```

Every route that fetches data MUST have a `loading.tsx` and `error.tsx`.

# Images — always next/image, never <img>

```typescript
// CORRECT — next/image handles optimization, lazy loading, WebP conversion
import Image from "next/image"

<Image
  src={product.image_url}
  alt={product.name}
  width={400}
  height={400}
  className="object-cover rounded-lg"
/>

// WRONG — raw <img> tag
<img src={product.image_url} alt={product.name} />
```

For Cloudinary images use the `fill` prop with a relative container:
```typescript
<div className="relative aspect-square">
  <Image src={cloudinaryUrl} alt={name} fill className="object-cover" />
</div>
```

# Metadata and SEO — always export generateMetadata

```typescript
// app/(site)/(public)/product/[slug]/page.tsx
import type { Metadata } from "next"
import { getProduct } from "@/lib/api/products"

export async function generateMetadata({ params }): Promise<Metadata> {
  const product = await getProduct(params.slug)
  return {
    title: `${product.name} | LSB Shop`,
    description: product.description,
    openGraph: {
      images: [product.image_url],
    },
  }
}
```

All public pages (catalog, product detail, home) must export `generateMetadata`.

# API client — three contexts, three functions

Auth uses **session cookies** (next-auth), NOT JWT/Bearer. Never add Authorization headers.

```typescript
// ── 1. CLIENT-SIDE or public Server Components ──────────────────────────────
// lib/api/client.ts → apiGet, apiPost, apiPatch, apiDelete
// Use when: Client Component fetch, or Server Component for PUBLIC data (no session needed)
import { apiGet } from "@/lib/api/client"
const products = await apiGet<PaginatedResponse<DrfProduct>>(`/api/v1/products/?${qs}`)

// ── 2. SERVER-ONLY reads that need the session cookie ───────────────────────
// lib/api/server-django.ts → serverFetchJson
// Use when: Server Component or Server Action reads that require staff auth
import { serverFetchJson } from "@/lib/api/server-django"
const orders = await serverFetchJson<PaginatedResponse<DrfOrder>>("/api/v1/orders/")
// Automatically forwards the session cookie from the incoming request

// ── 3. MUTATIONS from Server Actions ────────────────────────────────────────
// lib/api/server-django.ts → serverMutationJson
// Use when: "use server" actions that POST/PATCH/DELETE to Django
"use server"
import { serverMutationJson } from "@/lib/api/server-django"
await serverMutationJson("/api/v1/products/", "POST", payload)

// ── 4. ROUTE HANDLERS as proxy (app/api/…/route.ts) ─────────────────────────
// Use ONLY when a Client Component needs to call Django with session auth
// (CORS + cookie forwarding prevent direct calls from the browser)
// Current route handlers: /api/products/load-more, /api/sign-cloudinary-params
```

**Decision rule:**
- Public data, any context → `apiGet`
- Server Component / Server Action reading auth-protected data → `serverFetchJson`
- Mutation → Server Action + `serverMutationJson`
- Client Component needs Django data it can't get via Server Props → Route Handler proxy

# Naming conventions

- Components: `PascalCase` → `ProductCard.tsx`
- Hooks: `camelCase` with `use` prefix → `useCartActions.ts`
- Store: `camelCase` with `Store` suffix → `useUIStore.ts`
- Utils: `camelCase` · Types: `PascalCase` · Constants: `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE`
- Route segments: `kebab-case`

# Forms — React Hook Form + Zod always

```typescript
const loginSchema = z.object({
  email: z.string().email("Email inválido"),
  password: z.string().min(8, "Mínimo 8 caracteres"),
})
type LoginForm = z.infer<typeof loginSchema>

// Submit button disabled while pending, field errors shown below each input
// Never use uncontrolled inputs for forms
```

# UI rules

- Loading: always show `<ComponentSkeleton />` while fetching
- Error: always show `<ErrorState message="..." onRetry={refetch} />`
- Empty: always show `<EmptyState title="..." description="..." />`
- Toasts: always human language — never `toast.error(error.message)`
- Images: always `next/image` — never `<img>`
- Styles: only Tailwind — never inline styles
- `cn()` from `lib/utils.ts` for conditional classes

# Error messages shown to users

| Situation | Message |
|---|---|
| Session expired | "Tu sesión ha expirado. Vuelve a iniciar sesión." |
| No permissions | "No tienes permisos para realizar esta acción." |
| Out of stock | "Este producto no tiene stock disponible." |
| Payment failed | "El pago no pudo procesarse. Verifica tus datos." |
| Network error | "Sin conexión. Comprueba tu red." |
| Generic error | "Algo salió mal. Inténtalo de nuevo en unos minutos." |
